The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Wednesday, August 17, 2005 

 Scholarship

 Calcutta, Aug. 16: The state government has decided to increase the scholarships for those doing research projects in state-aided varsities, particularly those in Calcutta and Jadavpur universities, reports our special correspondent.

 Speaking in Calcutta University, higher education minister Satyasadhan Chakraborty today said the state is working out a plan to improve the quality of research in universities and the decision to increase the scholarship is part of the scheme. 

 The plan is awaiting the finance departments nod. 




